hpnicfDHCPServer.name: hpnicfDHCPServer
hpnicfDHCPServer.description: The MIB module is used for DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPServerIPPoolUsage.name: hpnicfDHCPServerIPPoolUsage
hpnicfDHCPServerIPPoolUsage.description: Usage factor of DHCP server ip pool.

hpnicfDHCPServerReqTimes.name: hpnicfDHCPServerReqTimes
hpnicfDHCPServerReqTimes.description: Number of requests received by the DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes.name: hpnicfDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes
hpnicfDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes.description: Number of requests success responses sent by the DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold.name: hpnicfDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold
hpnicfDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold.description: Threshold of average IP usage of a DHCP server pool in 5 minutes.

hpnicfDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold.name: hpnicfDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold
hpnicfDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold.description: Threshold of maximum IP usage of a DHCP server pool in 5 minutes.

hpnicfDHCPServerAllocateThreshold.name: hpnicfDHCPServerAllocateThreshold
hpnicfDHCPServerAllocateThreshold.description: Threshold of DHCP server allocated IP address in 5 minutes.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting a global pool for the DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.description: A table containing the configurations of dhcp server global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the network ip or host ip etc. to global pools for DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType.description: Type of a DHCP global pool. Any operations of this object will be bound with the operations of hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork, hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr, or hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr. That means any operation of this object alone will be regarded as invalid operation.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork.description: Network ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 1.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(network). The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a network ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.description: Host ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 2.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(host) The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a host ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP global pool(host). To delete a configured hardware address, please set hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 3.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag.description: Flag of undo operation for hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr.description: Start IP of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured start IP, please set hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr to 0. It takes effect only when hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr.description: End ip of a DHCP global pool.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable.description: A table for configuring parameters to DHCP global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for the configurations of parameters of DHCP global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited.description: A flag denoting if the lease of a pool is unlimited.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr.description: String of gateway ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip ip at a time.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo.description: A gateway ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of gateway router.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo.description: A DNS server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of DNS server.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr.description: String of NetBios server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, so a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo.description: A NetBios server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of NetBios server.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset.description: Reset the auto binding ip of the given global pool for DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime.description: Number of timeticks of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP.description: The Primary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client. To delete a configured Primary DNS server IP, please set hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP to 0. It takes effect only when hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP.description: The Secondary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client. To delete a configured Secondary DNS server IP, please set hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP to 0. It takes effect only when hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond.description: Number of seconds of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring options to DHCP global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring options to DHCP global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString.description: Hex string of an option. 1st to 16th hex strings, which are 2 bytes, 4 bytes, 6 bytes or 8 bytes, can be configured at most simultaneously. That means the format of each string must be '12', '1234', '123456' or '12345678'.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString.description: IP string of an option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable.description: The statistics of each DHCP address pool.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry.description: An entry containing the statistics of each DHCP address pool.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage.description: Utilization rate of IP addresses in each DHCP address pool, in percentage.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes.description: Number of request packets received by each DHCP address pool, including the request packets for an extension of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes.description: Number of positive responses sent by each DHCP address pool, including responses to the request for an extension of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes.description: Number of discover packets received by each DHCP address pool.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes.description: Number of offer packets sent by each DHCP address pool.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes.description: Number of ACK packets sent by each DHCP address pool.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolTotalIpNum.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolTotalIpNum
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolTotalIpNum.description: Number of IP addresses in each DHCP address pool.

hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolInUsedIpNum.name: hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolInUsedIpNum
hpnicfDHCPSrvGlbPoolInUsedIpNum.description: Number of allocated IP addresses in each DHCP address pool.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupTable
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server global option groups.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupEntry
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting a global option group.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupRowstatus.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupRowstatus
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionGroupRowstatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionTable
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionTable.description: A table for configuring options in a global option group.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionEntry
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionEntry.description: An entry containing objects for configuring an option in a global option group.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionHexString.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionHexString
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionHexString.description: Hex string of an option. 1 to 16 hex strings, which are 2 bytes, 4 bytes, 6 bytes or 8 bytes, can be configured at most simultaneously. That means the format of each string must be '12', '1234', '123456' or '12345678'.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionIPString.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionIPString
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionIPString.description: Ip string of an option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously.

hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionRowstatus.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionRowstatus
hpnicfDHCPSvrOptionRowstatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacTable
hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacTable.description: A table containing the verifying switches status for pools.

hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacEntry
hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacEntry.description: An entry containing the switch status for a pool.

hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacSwitch.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacSwitch
hpnicfDHCPSvrVerifyMacSwitch.description: The switch status for this pool. It has two defined values: enabled and disabled. If the value is enabled, the DHCP server only allocates IP address to host in the MAC list. The default value is disabled.

hpnicfDHCPSvrPoolMacTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSvrPoolMacTable
hpnicfDHCPSvrPoolMacTable.description: A table containing the MAC addresses list for pools.

hpnicfDHCPSvrPoolMacRowstatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDHCPServerAddrExhaust.description: This trap is generated when the device DHCP server address exhaust.

hpnicfDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover.name: hpnicfDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover
hpnicfDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover.description: This trap is generated when the device DHCP server address exhaust recover.
